<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-B62193CB-23E6-489E-A6EB-D1079948B98D" version="3" lang="en-US"?><tsTroubleshooting xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-B62193CB-23E6-489E-A6EB-D1079948B98D" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.2" domains="(topic tsTroubleshooting)                            (topic hi-d)    (topic sdlVariables-c)                             (topic ut-d)                             (topic indexing-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c tsTroubleshooting oceTroubleshooting-c)   " class="- topic/topic tsTroubleshooting/tsTroubleshooting "><title translate="no" class="- topic/title ">7923 CLE_MAINT_TRAY_LEVEL_SE (07B2) defect</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-B87BF88B-91B2-4C27-A55C-91B9B6986C8A"><p class="- topic/p ">Maintenance tray level sensor not activated within expected waste level. Possible causes: 
</p><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Real waste level in tray is significant lower then the estimated waste level
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Sensor is defect 
</p><note class="- topic/note " id="GUID-9F5C0CFC-AFE8-4A83-904F-28BEB2F1CD3D"><p class="- topic/p ">If current software version is below 4.3.0.0 first upgrade to the latest software version. 
</p></note></li></ol><p class="- topic/p ">On occurrence, this error will show an orange tile on the UI with the warning [Maintenance tray sensor broken] and it is not possible to replace the maintenance tray (replace button is greyed out). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">You can continue to use the current maintenance tray until a red tile on the UI with the warning [Replace the maintenance tray] appears. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">After occurrence of the red tile, 2 situations are possible. 
</p><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">If the level sensor became active in the period between above mentioned warnings, a new warning 7927 [CLE_MAINT_TRAY_LEVEL_SE 907B2) defect auto reset] is given and the maintenance tray can be replaced (replace button is active).] 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">If the level sensor stays inactive then it is not possible to replace the maintenance tray (replace button greyed out). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">A service call is required to recover from this situation by activating SDS test 07-6-107 [Reset permanent error of the maintenance tray]. Functional verification of the sensore is needed. 
</p></li></ol><note class="- topic/note " id="GUID-92CB1CC1-81F9-4B7D-9462-DA39386C082E"><p class="- topic/p ">After fixing the problem you need the following additional steps : 
</p><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Run SDS test 07-6-107 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Restart the system. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Replace the maintenance tray via the operator panel. 
</p></li></ol></note></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Diagnostics</category></metadata></prolog><tsBody class="- topic/body tsTroubleshooting/tsBody "><tsSymptoms id="GUID-33E1B64A-E818-4500-A780-C8BC692D14B2" class="- topic/section tsTroubleshooting/tsSymptoms "><p class="- topic/p "> 
</p></tsSymptoms><tsCauses id="GUID-51431842-B8B6-4201-AEC7-624FA5EFD0CA" class="- topic/section tsTroubleshooting/tsCauses "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Cleaning maintenance tray level sensor</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 07B2 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">CLE_MAINT_TRAY_LEVEL_SE</compsignal></comp> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">If the sensor is not broken, the following can also cause this warning: If the customer replaces the maintenance tray (before the level sensor is made) without using the wizard on the user interface (tools - replace maintenance tray) correctly, the level estimation is out of sync with the real ink level in the maintenance tray. The software expects the level sensor to be made based on the estimation. If the level sensor is not made within the expected area, this warning is generated and the maintenance tray cannot be replaced anymore (level won't be reset). A service call is required to recover from the situation. 
</p></tsCauses><tsDiagnose id="GUID-CD632E2D-E326-46ED-8FE0-08CBE1A57374" class="- topic/section tsTroubleshooting/tsDiagnose "><p class="- topic/p ">Check <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Cleaning maintenance tray level sensor</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 07B2 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">CLE_MAINT_TRAY_LEVEL_SE</compsignal></comp> 
</p></tsDiagnose><tsResolve id="GUID-B99BEB05-9B6C-47E1-91F5-3A151FA94DBC" class="- topic/section tsTroubleshooting/tsResolve "><table pgwide="1" id="GUID-F37B2244-A206-4555-9068-BB28101703B7" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="suspect" cols="6" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="15*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="25*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="15*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col4" colnum="4" colwidth="20*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col5" colnum="5" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col6" colnum="6" colwidth="15*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "/></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "/></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "/></entry><entry colname="col4" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "/></entry><entry colname="col5" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "/></entry><entry colname="col6" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "/></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><ph varid="SPP-Z-0704-1070127764" class="- topic/ph ">
          <xref href="PRTV2-SPP-0704-1070127764.xml" scope="external" type="extpl" format="html" class="- topic/xref "><?ditaot usertext?>Z-0704</xref>
        </ph> - 0028 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Test <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Cleaning maintenance tray level sensor</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 07B2 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">CLE_MAINT_TRAY_LEVEL_SE</compsignal></comp> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Fill a new maintenance tray with 0.8 liter of water to activate the level sensor. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><xref keyref="SDS07-2-102" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-CF7E3D6D-0472-40B4-9CCF-B575CE6F1EA4.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text xref?>07-2-102 Check CLE_MAINT_TRAY_LEVEL_SE (07B2) [Sensor Tests]</xref> 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Check 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Explain to the customer that the maintenance tray must be replaced following the instructions on the user interface. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col5" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><xref keyref="07COMP01" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-44445D33-A1AC-479B-B209-5A9AEC50FA1D.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="concept"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text xref?>07 The components of Maintenance and Tissue Wipe Unit</xref> 
